The paper presents a method for visualizing numerical data for map regions, which is a common topic in computer graphics (cs.GR) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The method involves enforcing constraints and measuring quality, which are common techniques in computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the importance of maintaining stability between different data values, which is relevant to information visualization (cs.SI).
